[{"category":"section","location":"api/#ExperimentsData","page":"API reference","text":"Data structures for defining an experimental test: the measurement, the loading/environmental protocol, the ambient conditions, and the specimen geometry. These four pieces are combined into an ExperimentData instance, which is the unit consumed by ConstitutiveModelling and ObjectiveFunctions.","title":"ExperimentsData"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#Test-presets","page":"API reference","text":"Ready-made ExperimentData specializations (e.g. UniaxialQuasiStaticTest, DielectricSpectroscopyTest) and their convenience constructors, for the common combinations of measurement/protocol/condition/geometry.","title":"Test presets"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#ConstitutiveModelling","page":"API reference","text":"Functions that evaluate a HyperFEM constitutive model against the protocol, condition, and geometry of an ExperimentData, predicting the dependent variable (stress, specific heat capacity, permittivity...) that ObjectiveFunctions compares against the measured data.","title":"ConstitutiveModelling"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#Reduced-kinematics","page":"API reference","text":"Internal kinematic maps (deformation gradient construction, thermal Jacobian solve) used by ConstitutiveModelling to reduce a 3D constitutive model to the 1D/2D loading states of a given Kinematics (uniaxial, biaxial).","title":"Reduced kinematics"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#ObjectiveFunctions","page":"API reference","text":"Predefined loss functions that evaluate the mismatch between observed data and the data predicted by ConstitutiveModelling, for a given constitutive model, a set of parameters, and one or more ExperimentData. These are the functions you minimize (e.g. with Optim.jl) during calibration.","title":"ObjectiveFunctions"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.AbstractCondition","page":"API reference","text":"Abstract type holding the static primary variables of the experimental test, such as the isothermal conditions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.AbstractCondition"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.AbstractGeometry","page":"API reference","text":"Abstract type holding the geometry of the specimen being tested.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.AbstractGeometry"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.AbstractMeasurement","page":"API reference","text":"Abstract type holding the quantity of interest of the experimental test.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.AbstractMeasurement"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.AbstractProtocol","page":"API reference","text":"Abstract type holding the dynamic primary variables of the experimental test, such as the sequence of strains.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.AbstractProtocol"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.Biaxial","page":"API reference","text":"Biaxial kinematics allow to evaluate the stress response at one Gauss point.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.Biaxial"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.CreepProtocol","page":"API reference","text":"A sequence of times at a constant stretch.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.CreepProtocol"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.CyclicLoadingProtocol","page":"API reference","text":"A sequence of stretches at a constant rate and time step.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.CyclicLoadingProtocol"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.DielectricMeasurement","page":"API reference","text":"The dielectric parmittivity recoded during a dielectric test.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.DielectricMeasurement"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.ElectricalCondition","page":"API reference","text":"An experiment at a constant voltage.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.ElectricalCondition"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.ExperimentData","page":"API reference","text":"ExperimentData{M, P, C, G}\n\nAn experiment holds a measurement M that is a function of a Protocol P -defining the independent variables- and conditionc C -environtmental static variables- and geometry G -for the reference specimen configuration-. Additionally, a weight can be assigned to the experiment to define its importance in the calibration process.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.ExperimentData"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.FrequencySweepProtocol","page":"API reference","text":"A sequence of frequencies.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.FrequencySweepProtocol"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.IsothermalCondition","page":"API reference","text":"An experiment at a constant temperature.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.IsothermalCondition"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.Kinematics","page":"API reference","text":"Abstract type dfining the mechanical loading protocol such as Uniaxial or Biaxial, allowing to compute the deformation gradient at one Gauss point.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.Kinematics"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.MechanicalTest","page":"API reference","text":"Super type for ExperimentData with mechanical measurement (stress) and mechanical protocol (stretch).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.MechanicalTest"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.PlateGeometry","page":"API reference","text":"A specimen geometry with a reference thickness and cross-sectional area.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.PlateGeometry"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.QuasiStaticProtocol","page":"API reference","text":"A sequence of stretches.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.QuasiStaticProtocol"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.SequentialProtocol","page":"API reference","text":"A sequential protocol defines a series of sub-protocols to be executed in order. E.g. a relaxation test is defined by a fast loading stage (CyclicLoadingProtocol) followed by a long holding stage (CreepProtocol).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.SequentialProtocol"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.StandardCondition","page":"API reference","text":"A standard condition with no additional parameters.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.StandardCondition"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.TemperatureSweepProtocol","page":"API reference","text":"A sequence of temperatures at constant rate.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.TemperatureSweepProtocol"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.TensileMeasurement","page":"API reference","text":"The nominal stress recoded during a tensile test.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.TensileMeasurement"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.ThermalMeasurement","page":"API reference","text":"The specific heat capacity recoded during a thermal test.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.ThermalMeasurement"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.ThermalTest","page":"API reference","text":"Super type fo ExperimentData with thermal measurement (specific heat capacity) and thermal protocol (temperature).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.ThermalTest"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.ThermoDielectricTest","page":"API reference","text":"Super type for ExperimentData with dielectric measurement (permittivity) and thermal protocol (temperature).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.ThermoDielectricTest"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.ThermoElectricalCondition","page":"API reference","text":"An experiment at a constant temperature and voltage.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.ThermoElectricalCondition"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.Uniaxial","page":"API reference","text":"Uniaxial kinematics allow to evaluate the stress response at one Gauss point.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.Uniaxial"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.electric_field-Tuple{HyperCalibration.AbstractCondition, HyperCalibration.AbstractGeometry}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the electric field for a given condition and geometry.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.electric_field"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.frequencies-Tuple{HyperCalibration.AbstractProtocol}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the sequence of frequencies for a given protocol.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.frequencies"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.independent_variable-Tuple{HyperCalibration.AbstractProtocol}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the sequence of the independent variable for a given protocol.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.independent_variable"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.max_stretch-Tuple{HyperCalibration.AbstractProtocol}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the maximum stretch for a givben protocol.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.max_stretch"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.rate-Tuple{HyperCalibration.AbstractProtocol}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the rate of independent variable increment for a given protocol.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.rate"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.stretches-Tuple{HyperCalibration.AbstractProtocol}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the sequence of stretches for a given protocol.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.stretches"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.temperature-Tuple{HyperCalibration.AbstractCondition}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the room temperature for a given condition.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.temperature"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.temperatures-Tuple{HyperCalibration.AbstractProtocol}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the sequence of temperatures for a given protocol.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.temperatures"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.thickness-Tuple{HyperCalibration.AbstractGeometry}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the thickness for a given geometry.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.thickness"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.time_step-Tuple{HyperCalibration.AbstractProtocol}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the constant time step for a given protocol.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.time_step"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.voltage-Tuple{HyperCalibration.AbstractCondition}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the applied voltage for a given condition.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.voltage"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.DielectricSpectroscopyTest","page":"API reference","text":"Experiment data with frequency-dielectric permittivity (BDS).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.DielectricSpectroscopyTest"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.DifferentialScanningCalorimetryTest","page":"API reference","text":"Experiment data with temperature-specific heat capacity (DSC).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.DifferentialScanningCalorimetryTest"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.UniaxialCyclicLoadingTest","page":"API reference","text":"Experiment data with constant rate uniaxial stretch-stress and standard conditions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.UniaxialCyclicLoadingTest"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.UniaxialQuasiStaticTest","page":"API reference","text":"Experiment data with uniaxial quasi-static stretch-stress and standard conditions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.UniaxialQuasiStaticTest"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.UniaxialRelaxationTest","page":"API reference","text":"Experiment data with uniaxial relaxation stressess and standard conditions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.UniaxialRelaxationTest"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.UniaxialThermalCyclicLoadingTest","page":"API reference","text":"Experiment data with constant rate uniaxial stretch-stress and thermal conditions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.UniaxialThermalCyclicLoadingTest"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.UniaxialThermalQuasiStaticTest","page":"API reference","text":"Experiment data with uniaxial quasi-static stretch-stress and thermal conditions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.UniaxialThermalQuasiStaticTest"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.UniaxialThermalRelaxationTest","page":"API reference","text":"Experiment data with uniaxial relaxation stressess and thermal conditions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.UniaxialThermalRelaxationTest"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.UniaxialThermoElectricCyclicLoadingTest","page":"API reference","text":"Experiment data with constant rate uniaxial stretch-stress and coupled thermo-electrical conditions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.UniaxialThermoElectricCyclicLoadingTest"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.evaluate_cv-Tuple{HyperFEM.PhysicalModels.ThermoMechano, TemperatureSweepProtocol, HyperCalibration.AbstractCondition, HyperCalibration.AbstractGeometry}","page":"API reference","text":"Evaluate the specific heat capacity predicted by a constitutive model under the given thermal protocol, conditions and geometry of an experimental test.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.evaluate_cv"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.evaluate_epsilon-Tuple{HyperFEM.PhysicalModels.ThermoElectro, TemperatureSweepProtocol, HyperCalibration.AbstractCondition, HyperCalibration.AbstractGeometry}","page":"API reference","text":"Evaluate the dielectric permittivity predicted by a constitutive model under the given thermal protocol, conditions and geometry of an experimental test.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.evaluate_epsilon"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.evaluate_stress-Union{Tuple{K}, Tuple{HyperFEM.PhysicalModels.Elasto, HyperCalibration.MechanicalProtocol{K}, HyperCalibration.AbstractCondition, HyperCalibration.AbstractGeometry}} where K<:HyperCalibration.Kinematics","page":"API reference","text":"Evaluate the stress predicted by a constitutive model under the given mechanical protocol, conditions, and geometry of an experimental test.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.evaluate_stress"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.F_volumetric-Tuple{Real}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the isotropic (volumetric) deformation gradient corresponding to a given Jacobian J, i.e. F = J^(1/3) * I.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.F_volumetric"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.J_thermal-Tuple{HyperFEM.PhysicalModels.PhysicalModel, Float64}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the thermally-induced volumetric Jacobian J for a given physical model and temperature. Defaults to 1.0 (no thermal expansion) for models that do not couple volume to temperature.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.J_thermal"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.J_thermal-Tuple{HyperFEM.PhysicalModels.PhysicalModel, HyperCalibration.AbstractCondition}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the thermally-induced volumetric Jacobian for a given physical model and AbstractCondition, by extracting the temperature from the condition. Defaults to 1.0 for models that do not couple volume to temperature.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.J_thermal"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.J_thermal-Tuple{HyperFEM.PhysicalModels.ThermalVolumetric, Float64}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the thermally-induced volumetric Jacobian J for a ThermalVolumetric model at a given temperature θ, solved by a Newton iteration on the zero-pressure condition pressure(J) = 0.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.J_thermal"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.J_thermal-Tuple{HyperFEM.PhysicalModels.ThermoMechano, HyperCalibration.AbstractCondition}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the thermally-induced volumetric Jacobian for a ThermoMechano model under the given AbstractCondition.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.J_thermal"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.calculate_F-Tuple{HyperFEM.PhysicalModels.PhysicalModel, Float64}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the purely volumetric deformation gradient for a given physical model at temperature θ, with the Jacobian solved by J_thermal.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.calculate_F"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.calculate_F-Tuple{HyperFEM.PhysicalModels.PhysicalModel, Real, Real, HyperCalibration.AbstractCondition}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the deformation gradient for an independently biaxial test with stretches λ1 and λ2 under the given AbstractCondition, including any thermally-induced volumetric contribution.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.calculate_F"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.calculate_F-Tuple{HyperFEM.PhysicalModels.PhysicalModel, Type{Biaxial}, Real, HyperCalibration.AbstractCondition}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the deformation gradient for a Biaxial kinematics test at stretch λ under the given AbstractCondition, including any thermally-induced volumetric contribution.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.calculate_F"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.calculate_F-Tuple{HyperFEM.PhysicalModels.PhysicalModel, Type{Uniaxial}, Real, HyperCalibration.AbstractCondition}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the deformation gradient for a Uniaxial kinematics test at stretch λ under the given AbstractCondition, including any thermally-induced volumetric contribution.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.calculate_F"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.experiment_prediction-Tuple{HyperFEM.PhysicalModels.PhysicalModel, MechanicalTest}","page":"API reference","text":"Return the y_true and y_pred sampling points for a given constitutive model and experimental test.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.experiment_prediction"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#HyperCalibration.loss-Tuple{HyperFEM.PhysicalModels.PhysicalModel, ExperimentData}","page":"API reference","text":"Compute the loss function for a given constitutive model and one/multiple experimental tests as the weighted normalized squared difference between the predicted and the measured values.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HyperCalibration.loss"},{"category":"section","location":"ext/","page":"Extensions","text":"HyperCalibration.jl uses Julia's package extension mechanism ([weakdeps] / [extensions] in Project.toml) to add optional functionality that only loads when the corresponding package is also loaded. Neither extension changes the core API described in ExperimentsData / ConstitutiveModelling / ObjectiveFunctions — they add convenience methods on top of it.","title":"Extensions"},{"category":"section","location":"ext/#CSV-loading-—-ExperimentsCSVExt","page":"Extensions","text":"Loaded automatically when CSV is loaded alongside HyperCalibration. Adds a CSV.read method that parses a CSV file directly into a vector of ExperimentData:\n\nusing HyperCalibration, CSV\n\nexperiments = CSV.read(\"quasi_static_tests.csv\", UniaxialQuasiStaticTest)\n\nRows are grouped by an id column, and one ExperimentData is built per group. The expected columns depend on the target test type — e.g. UniaxialQuasiStaticTest expects id, stretch, stress; a thermal variant such as UniaxialThermalCyclicLoadingTest additionally expects vel and temp. A thickness keyword can be passed for tests that need a specimen thickness (UniaxialThermoElectricCyclicLoadingTest); it defaults to 0.0 otherwise.\n\nSupported target types are the test presets in ExperimentsInterface.jl. Requesting an unsupported type raises an error prompting you to add a build_experiment method for it.","title":"CSV loading — ExperimentsCSVExt"},{"category":"section","location":"ext/#Plotting-—-HyperCalibrationPlots","page":"Extensions","text":"Loaded automatically when Plots is loaded alongside HyperCalibration. Adds Plots.jl recipes for visually comparing a constitutive model's predictions against experimental data:\n\nusing HyperCalibration, HyperFEM, Plots\n\nplot(model, experiments[1], xlabel=\"Stretch [-]\", ylabel=\"Stress [KPa]\", units_scale=1e-3)\n\nplot(model::PhysicalModel, data::ExperimentData) draws the model prediction as a line and the measured data as a scatter series over the data's independent_variable.\nplot(model::PhysicalModel, datasets::AbstractVector{<:ExperimentData}) overlays one series pair per experiment; pass label and/or seriescolor as vectors (one entry per experiment) to control each series individually.\nunits_scale rescales both predicted and measured values before plotting (e.g. 1e-3 to display stress in kPa instead of Pa).","title":"Plotting — HyperCalibrationPlots"},{"category":"section","location":"#HyperCalibration.jl","page":"Home","text":"(Image: Stable) (Image: Dev) (Image: Build Status) (Image: Aqua QA)\n\nTools for the calibration of hyperelastic constitutive models, built on top of HyperFEM.jl.\n\nThe main components of the package are:\n\nExperimentData: a data structure holding the definition of an experimental test.\nconstitutive modelling: a set of functions that evaluate a constitutive model from HyperFEM with the data from an experiment and predicts the dependent variable.\nobjective functions: predefined loss function that evaluates the difference from observed data and predicted data with a given constitutive model, a set of parameters, and a set of experiments.","title":"HyperCalibration.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#How-to-use","page":"Home","text":"The package is a registered package, and can be installed with Pkg.add.\n\njulia> using Pkg; Pkg.add(\"Optim\")\n\nor through the pkg REPL mode by typing\n\n] add HyperCalibration","title":"How to use"},{"category":"section","location":"#Example","page":"Home","text":"using HyperCalibration, HyperFEM\nusing Optim\nusing CSV\nusing Plots\n\nexperiments = CSV.read(joinpath(@__DIR__, \"quasi_static_tests.csv\"), UniaxialQuasiStaticTest, decimal='.')\n\nbuild_model(μ, N) = EightChain(μ=μ, N=N)\npn = [  \"μ\",   \"N\"]  # Parameter names\np0 = [  1e4,   1.0]  # Initial seed\n\nf(p) = loss(build_model, p, experiments)\n\nresult = optimize(f, p0, NelderMead())\nmodel = build_model(result.minimizer...)\nplot(model, experiments[1], xlabel=\"Stretch [-]\", ylabel=\"Stress [KPa]\", units_scale=1e-3)","title":"Example"},{"category":"section","location":"#Project-funded-by","page":"Home","text":"Grants PID2022-141957OA-C22/PID2022-141957OB-C22 funded by MCIN/AEI/ 10.13039/501100011033","title":"Project funded by"}]
